[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    105[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   - Step 9 `persist_recruitment_decision`: route the structural decision-record (decision_id, session_id, trial_id, prospective_participant_id_hash, disposition, version stamps, timestamp) to DynamoDB with archive references (`composed_response_archive_ref`, `tool_calls_archive_ref`, `citations_archive_ref`, `prescreen_responses_archive_ref`); full content routes to a per-trial Object-Lock S3 prefix with the recruitment-decision-record-journal customer-managed KMS key. The Python companion already does this at the function level per the prior code review; promote to architectural primitive in the pseudocode walkthrough.
